105
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:07,524
Lisbeth.

106
00:07:07,727 --> 00:07:09,922
Mr. Dirch Frode.

107
00:07:10,129 --> 00:07:11,926
How do you do?

108
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:24,800
Something wrong
with the report?

109
00:07:25,011 --> 00:07:26,569
FRODE:
No, it was quite thorough.

110
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:29,646
But I'm also interested
in what's not in it.

111
00:07:29,849 --> 00:07:32,818
There's nothing not in it.
Your opinion of him isn't.

112
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:36,811
I'm not paid to give my opinion.
So you don't have one?

113
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:41,950
He's clean,
in my opinion.

114
00:07:42,161 --> 00:07:44,686
You mean he's hygienic?

115
00:07:45,164 --> 00:07:48,827
He's who he presents himself to be.
In his business, that's an asset.

116
00:07:49,035 --> 00:07:52,129
Well, there's less
in his asset column after
his conviction today.

117
00:07:52,338 --> 00:07:54,135
True. He made a fool of himself.

118
00:07:54,340 --> 00:07:55,807
If it happened that way.

119
00:07:56,008 --> 00:07:57,976
Are you suggesting
that he was set up?

120
00:07:58,978 --> 00:08:00,741
